# web

## providers
- label: the web token report recognizes Antigravity CLI as the agy provider when agy usage is present
  command: grep -q '"agy"' packages/web/lib/types.ts && grep -q 'Antigravity CLI' packages/web/lib/analytics.ts && grep -q '"agy"' packages/web/scripts/publish-usage.ts && grep -q 'agy:' packages/cli/src/graph.ts
  tags: [implemented]
- label: the web token report presents Gemini CLI history as part of the Antigravity CLI provider row
  command: grep -Fq 'agy: "Antigravity CLI"' packages/web/lib/analytics.ts && ! grep -R 'Gemini CLI successor' packages/cli/src packages/web/app packages/web/lib packages/web/scripts packages/web/test packages/cli/test
  tags: [implemented]
- the CLI reads Antigravity CLI generation metadata from ~/.gemini/antigravity-cli/conversations and publishes agy token totals when usage blobs are present @implemented
- the web report only shows the Antigravity CLI no-data state when neither legacy Gemini CLI nor current agy rows are published @implemented
- label: the published web report folds legacy Gemini CLI and current agy usage into one Antigravity CLI provider row instead of describing agy as a Gemini CLI successor
  command: bunx tsx --test --test-name-pattern 'folds Gemini CLI history' packages/web/test/publish-usage.test.ts && grep -Fq 'foldGeminiIntoAntigravityProvider' packages/web/scripts/publish-usage.ts
  tags: [implemented]

## design
- label: the web report uses a flat reference-font background, white heatmap cells, and a conditional Antigravity no-data state
  command: grep -Fq 'background: var(--color-bg);' packages/web/app/globals.css && grep -Fq '["#f5f5f5", "#ffffff"]' packages/web/lib/usage.ts && grep -Fq 'No published Antigravity CLI usage yet' packages/web/app/svg-usage.tsx && grep -Fq 'colorMode: "light"' packages/web/scripts/publish-usage.ts
  tags: [implemented]
